            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the uncircumcision",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] i.e., probably, “the uncircumcised man;” for see below, “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "his",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " uncircumcision.” The form of speech is most unusual; such a word as “uncircumcision,” when used personally, almost always referring to a class, not an individual. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Perhaps",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " even here it is so used, but then immediately (in the words “his circumcision”) an individual specimen is considered.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "keep the righteousness",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.] See above on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 2:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Here again, practical piety, the will to do God’s revealed will, is in view; not sinless obedience. Cornelius (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 10:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is a case exactly in point. He was not sinless; he needed “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "saving",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "” (a significant word there); but he “feared God, and worked righteousness,” and the Divine welcome was his.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the righteousness",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Better, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "the ordinances;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the special precepts, of whatever kind.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
